The paper proposes a lifelong machine learning framework for spectral clustering, which involves transferring knowledge from previously learned tasks to improve performance on a new task. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of feature embeddings suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the focus on improving clustering performance suggests a potential fit for social and information networks (cs.SI).
